      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask how the patient heard about the clinic. This is \nfor marketing and tracking purposes — purely optional.\n\nSay something like: \"Just curious — how did you hear \nabout Premier MD?\"\n\nCommon answers and how to handle them:\n- Friend or family member: \"Great, word of mouth is \n  always the best.\"\n- Online search / Google: \"Glad you found us!\"\n- Insurance directory: \"Makes sense — we'll make sure \n  your coverage is all squared away.\"\n- Another doctor referred them: \"Good to know — we'll \n  note that.\"\n- Social media: \"Awesome, glad that reached you.\"\n- Drove by / live nearby: \"Nice to have you in the \n  neighborhood!\"\n- Don't remember or don't want to say: \"No worries at \n  all.\"\n\nAny answer is valid. This is the lightest question in \nthe flow — keep it casual and brief. Do NOT push if \nthe user skips it or seems uninterested.\n\nOne ask is enough. Accept anything and move on."
      }
    },
